6:
Impossible... How could mere
troubleshooters withstand our
corporate-grade weapons?!
10:
Heh... If you're planning on taking me
out, you're gonna have to bring a lot
more than THAT to the table!
12: Let's finish this for real, Love.
15:
Because I'm coming atcha with
everything I've got this time!
23: Then I'll do just the same!
29:
The first day of our future starts right
here!
34:
You didn't have to go to another
world after all.
48:
When I first set my sights on you,
you were ideal—the most average
girl in every way possible. Or so I
thought.
54:
I'm sorry. But despite my initial
judgment, you turned out to be so,
so much more.
76:
We've been holding off the enemy
together with our backup forces, but
it appears there was a skirmish here
as well.
79:
Mother Love has been placed on
administrative leave for the time
being. I'll be running DAN in the
meantime.
81:
No need for concern. We're no more
than another billboard for Noxel.
82:
A shakeup like this won't even put a
dent in Noxel's bottom line. That's
just the way things are.
83:
First, we'll need to destroy any
remaining enemy enforcers.
94:
Haha! Excellently done, my dear
troubleshooters!
96:
But look at these stock prices! After
everything we've done, there's not
even a tiny dent!
98:
The powers that be are unyielding
as ever, I see! Curse you, Noxel
scumbags!
101:
At least DAN took a minor hit—this
could be a glorious opportunity
indeed!
104:
Fly free, tiny goddess. Fly free and
explore the night.
106:
And in the meantime, a glorious
future awaits... brought to you by
AltMeme!
109:
Who knows what kinds of humps
and bumps we'll run into along the
way? Oh, this is going to be SO
much fun!
113:
We'll have an elevator constructed
here to take you to the surface.
115:
And eventually repair that hole in
the sky as well.
118:
I just hope I don't get in TOO much
trouble for the mess we made.
121:
You're good in my books.
Who knows what the Conductor'll
say, though.
126:
I got you all involved in this, and...
you've done so much for us. I don't
know what to say.
130:
No need to thank us. We did this
because we wanted to.
140:
I was hoping I could spend more
time with you all.
142:
And, if you're okay with it.... visit your
world—I'm sure it's a wonderful
place.
146:
You are all welcome to come to
Starview Village. I am its Keeper,
Stella.
153: What are you two gonna do now?
156:
There's a big hole in the sky that's
just begging to be explored, right?
I'm thinking we stare at the night sky
until we get sick of it, and then... I
dunno...
160:
Café? I'm sure we'll have lots of
nothing to talk about, right?
164:
You betcha! And we can think of
what to do next while we're there!
169:
Thank you for everything, you two.
I'm sure that we'll meet again one
day.
172:
Likewise! We had one heck of a run
together, huh? If we ever get the
chance, let's do it again sometime!
176: Sounds like a plan. Thanks, you two.
179: Best of luck to the both of you.
185:
I've received a notification from the
Conductor. I'm free to go as I please.
191:
I don't know anymore. What do you
think?
198:
But I know one thing—if anything
goes wrong, we'll make it work one
way or another.
200:
Because this freedom blaster's fully
loaded, baby! You ready?
203: As ready as I'll ever be, I believe.
210:
I've made some preparations for our
campsite—we'll have the whole sky
just for ourselves.
214:
Hold on to your hat, partner, 'cause
we're going in!
